ygData.messageBody:
Here is the link to EQCharinfo although it has changed it's name to
Everlogs.

http://www.gralin.com/everlogs/

This utility lets you look at separate sessions and combined sessions. I
think it does do a lot of the parsing that you are doing by hand John.

Tomerrilin Loreweaver

From: kim@... [mailto:kim@...]

Subject: RE: [eqbards] L46 weapon effectiveness.


From: <kim@...>

On Thu, 17 Feb 2000, Kimes, Dean W. wrote:
>
> Hmm the parser I use has the ability to attach logfiles to a character for
> processing. It appends them together to keep a full record unless you
> delete them after processing. This parser has some interesting abilities

Heh. That's the thing - I *don't* want a full record. I cut
my logfiles up into different stat/equipment configurations
and parse each one seperately.

> but they don;t seem to work properly for bards. The two I use are
> Eqcharinfo and eqparser I think, but I don't remember offhand which is
> which.

Where'd you get them?

--
John H. Kim
